‘‘(a) IN GENERAL.—The Coast Guard shall administer laws, promulgate and en-
force regulations, and engage in operations and activities, with due regard to the
requirements of national defense, in support of the following:
‘‘(1) NON-HOMELANDSECURITYMISSIONS.—
‘‘(A) MARINE SAFETY.—Engage in oceanographic research, ensure the safe
operation of and facilitate the economical movement of goods through the
Marine Transportation System, and develop, establish, maintain, and oper-
ate rescue facilities for the promotion of safety on, under, and over the high
seas and waters subject to the jurisdiction of the United States and protect
