‘‘(B) SEARCH AND RESCUE.—Respond to maritime disasters, natural or
man-made, and render aid to people in distress to protect the lives and pro-
mote the safety of life and property on, under, and over the high seas and
waters subject to the jurisdiction of the United States, covering all matters
not specifically delegated by law to some other executive department.
