SEC. 407. INTERNATIONAL MARITIME OIL SPILL RESPONSE.
(a) INGENERAL.—Not later than 180 days after the date of enactment of this Act,
the Commandant shall, in coordination with the Secretary of State, review and up-
date the Canada-US Joint Maritime Pollution Contingency Plan.
(b) REQUIREMENTS.—In carrying out subsection (a), the Commandant shall—
(1) review each geographic annex within the contingency plan;
(2) analyze the vessel traffic patterns, including the types of vessels transiting
the area, and assess the risks of a pollution incident; and
(3) determine if any of the areas should be expanded or modified.
(c) EXERCISES.—The Commandant, in coordination with the Secretary of State,
shall conduct a joint training exercise not less than once a year to determine emer-
gency response capabilities and identify other types of support necessary to effec-
tuate a successful oil spill response, in accordance with the Canada-US Joint Mari-
time Pollution Contingency Plan.
