Section 271. Policy and briefing on availability of naloxone to treat
opioid, including fentanyl, overdoses
This section requires the Commandant to update the policy of
the Coast Guard regarding the use of medication to treat drug
overdoses, including naloxone for fentanyl overdoses. The policy re-
quires access to such medication at Coast Guard facilities, onboard
Coast Guard assets, and during Coast Guard operations. It also re-
quires that all Coast Guard installations maintain a supply of
naloxone (or similar medication) to treat overdoses by Coast Guard
members or during interactions with the public.
